.TH IARGC 3F
.SH NAME
iargc \- return the number of command line arguments
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f3integer i
.br
.sp
i = iargc( )\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f2iargc\fR function returns the number of command
line arguments passed to the program.
Thus, if a program were invoked via
.br
.sp
	foo arg1 arg2 arg3
.br
.sp
\f2iargc( )\fR would return 3.
.SH SEE ALSO
getarg(3F).
